.TH RGX 1 "June 2026" "rgx" "Fish Functions"
.SH NAME
rgx \- rg + fzf + bat preview fuzzy content search
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rgx
[OPTIONS] PATTERN
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBrgx\fR is an interactive file content searcher that combines \fBrg\fR
(ripgrep), \fBfzf\fR, and \fBbat\fR. Results open in \fBnvim\fR at the
matching line.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-hidden\fR, \fB\-H\fR
Search hidden files and directories.
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Display usage information and exit.
.PP
Any additional arguments are passed through to \fBrg\fR(1) (e.g.,
\fB\-g\fR for glob, \fB\-t\fR for file type).
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.TP
Enter
Open selected file in editor at the matching line.
.TP
Ctrl+P
Paste selected paths to stdout.
.TP
Ctrl+Y
Yank selected paths to clipboard (wl-copy).
.TP
Ctrl+Space
Toggle file preview pane.
.TP
Tab
Select/deselect multiple rows.
.TP
Alt+H
Toggle hidden file visibility.
.TP
\(<-/\(->
Scroll preview line by line.
.TP
Ctrl+D/U
Scroll preview page up/down.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B rgx foo
Search for "foo" in current directory (recursive).
.TP
.B rgx \-\-hidden foo
Search hidden files too.
.TP
.B rgx \-g '*.py' foo
Search only Python files.
.TP
.B rgx \-t js foo
Search only JavaScript/TypeScript files.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rg (1),
.BR fzf (1),
.BR bat (1),
.BR fdx (1)
